Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:36.57,Ep_Title,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(550,600)}Tanaka's Revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.40,0:01:36.22,Default,PEDESTRIAN B,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.66,0:01:40.37,sign_2366_3_Maid_Cafe,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,Maid Café
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.66,0:01:40.37,sign_2366_4_Welcome_Back__Ma,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome Back, Master
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.28,0:01:45.09,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you! What are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.85,0:01:48.08,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Our story begins four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.62,0:01:51.94,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, I had just started \Nworking for a game company.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:53.72,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In order to examine our competitors' games,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:55.57,Flashback,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There's broad demand for the \Ncombination of intuitive puzzle games
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:55.88,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was playing several free-to-play games.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.57,0:01:57.22,Flashback,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and anime characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.54,0:01:59.22,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I don't like modern games.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.75,0:02:01.84,Flashback,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Last year, Namico's {\i1}Puzzle \NFantasy{\i0} made over 40 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.82,0:02:02.92,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Games are supposed to be \Nan escape from reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.42,0:02:06.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Having friends gives you an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.86,0:02:06.89,Flashback,COWORKER D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Seriously, I'd go if I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.23,0:02:08.45,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Having money and time \Ngives you an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.89,0:02:08.26,Flashback,COWORKER D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You never show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:10.53,Flashback,COWORKER E,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I promise I'll go next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.45,0:02:10.53,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's no different than reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:16.44,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Going back even further, when I was \Na third-year grade school student,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:16.95,Flashback,STUDENT A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey, that's the new Gandum!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:18.22,Flashback,STUDENT D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I won it in a giveaway!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:20.32,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,eraser collecting \Nwas briefly a fad in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.22,0:02:18.74,Flashback,STUDENT E,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Lemme see!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:19.92,Flashback,STUDENT F,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.82,0:02:30.83,sign_3401_27_Found_Around_Sch,CLASSROOM SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Found Around School
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.83,0:02:25.15,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was due to our homeroom teacher \Nbeing rather fussy about the wealth gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.15,0:02:27.05,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,All our possessions were standardized.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.05,0:02:30.83,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Students were instructed not to \Ndeviate from the average.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.87,0:02:36.53,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,However, there was one loophole: stationery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.95,0:02:40.25,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Among such products, a wide variety \Nof erasers were available in circulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.25,0:02:43.40,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,so as a class, we threw ourselves \Ninto collecting erasers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.13,0:02:43.40,Flashback,STUDENT A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.40,0:02:45.33,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Who had the most erasers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.33,0:02:46.64,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Who had the rarest erasers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.96,0:02:49.89,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That alone determined our class hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.77,0:02:54.18,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's an exaggeration. \NActually, it's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.18,0:02:57.91,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,As you might expect, \Nathletic kids, smart kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.91,0:03:01.99,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,strong fighters, attractive kids, \Nartistic kids, and funny kids
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:04.63,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,naturally stood near the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:07.66,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But for the rest of us \Nwho didn't have anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.04,0:03:07.74,Flashback,STUDENT K,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The PE teacher's shirt \Nwas hanging out during class.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.66,0:03:12.86,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,eraser collecting was our last hope \Nfor squeezing into the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.86,0:03:16.30,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is also an exaggeration and a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.30,0:03:19.39,Flashback,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Did you see his face when he noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.33,0:03:19.39,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Even among the kids who had nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.39,0:03:22.98,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,there were only two of us \Nwho collected erasers seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.98,0:03:25.80,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Me and another kid named Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:28.86,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Sato was a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:32.12,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,His parents frequently traveled for work, \Nwhich meant he was lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.12,0:03:34.14,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,He received an allowance as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.14,0:03:36.55,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and would ask his parents \Nto bring him back rare local erasers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.55,0:03:38.36,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,as souvenirs from their business trips.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:42.10,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I think the reason I participated
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.10,0:03:45.20,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,in this pointless showdown \Nbetween the two of us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.79,0:03:49.80,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,was because I already \Npossessed one rare eraser.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.20,0:03:52.54,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was an eraser shaped like a dodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:56.07,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My relatives bought it for me \Non an overseas trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:58.35,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I loved birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.35,0:04:01.80,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I read my bird encyclopedia again \Nand again until the pages wore out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.47,0:04:05.11,Flashback,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You're an unusual bird, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.43,0:04:13.19,sign_5909_64_Pet_House,STORE SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Pet House
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.59,0:04:11.98,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Once, I begged my father \Nto get me a pet bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:14.87,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My father took me into the pet shop with \Nthe understanding that we'd just look around,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.87,0:04:17.73,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but in the end, he bought me \Na gray male cockatiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:20.37,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I named him Maru.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.37,0:04:23.76,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Later he told my mother that he was \Nhelping cultivate my aesthetic sensibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.76,0:04:26.95,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but thinking on it, it was probably \Njust that he wasn't very expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:30.18,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,They bought my brother \Nthe expensive otaku computer games,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.18,0:04:32.51,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and Maru must've been cheap in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.78,0:04:36.18,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,While doing my best to care for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.18,0:04:38.99,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,a relationship of trust was born between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:41.55,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But back to my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.55,0:04:44.11,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My dodo eraser certainly was rare,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.38,0:04:45.73,Flashback,STUDENT A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sato-kun, where'd you get those?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.11,0:04:46.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but the erasers that \NI could afford on my allowance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:47.36,Flashback,STUDENT D,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.75,0:04:48.93,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,didn't stand a chance \Nagainst Sato's collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.36,0:04:48.93,Flashback,STUDENT E,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Can I touch them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:49.92,Flashback,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.27,0:04:52.67,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A tiny handful of students fawned over him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.67,0:04:55.42,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and I found it unbearably frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.83,0:05:00.02,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd smugly return to using an ordinary \Neraser after trying a bunch of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:02.36,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,or utter great insights like,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:05.95,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,"this is what they use instead of erasers \Nat art colleges," while using bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.95,0:05:09.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But those low-class techniques that I pretended \Nwere high-class were obviously ineffective,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.75,0:05:12.83,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and every day I tasted defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.75,0:05:15.18,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Then something happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:19.00,sign_7601_91_One_of_a_kind_Su,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,One-of-a-kind Super Rare Original Donraku Eraser
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.00,0:05:21.24,sign_7649_92_One_of_a_kind_Su,,0000,0000,0000,,One-of-a-kind Super Rare Original Donraku Eraser
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.95,0:05:23.59,Flashback,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A Donraku eraser...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.59,0:05:25.80,sign_7759_94_Auctions___Toys_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Auctions > Toys > Games > Figures > Erasers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.59,0:05:25.80,sign_7759_95_One_of_a_kind_Su,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,One-of-a-kind Super Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.03,0:05:31.71,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,"This is it," I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.71,0:05:34.11,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,There was only one of them in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:36.69,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was my only chance to turn things around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.69,0:05:37.81,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd show him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.52,0:05:41.07,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I returned home, and \Nonce my family was asleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.07,0:05:43.94,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I took my father's credit \Ncard from his wallet
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:45.77,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and wrote down his credit card number.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.07,0:05:52.52,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Considering how I was going to pay \Nfor it, I needed a credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.52,0:05:54.63,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was a typical card. \NOne accessible to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.63,0:05:56.98,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The kind of card a student might use.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.98,0:06:01.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,When I learned that later, \NI became a little sentimental,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:03.55,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but that's another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:08.07,Flashback,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,My dad bought this for me \Nwhen he went to Dubai.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.15,0:06:08.68,Flashback_Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Just you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.56,0:06:10.91,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That day, after leaving school,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.91,0:06:13.09,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,during the limited period \Nwhen my brother wasn't home,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:14.18,sign_8933_113_Number_of_Bids,TOP LEFT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Number of Bids
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:14.18,sign_8933_114_Bidding_History,TOP LEFT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Bidding History
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:14.18,sign_8933_115_Time_Remaining,TOP RIGHT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Time Remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:14.18,sign_8933_116_3_Days____Detail,TOP RIGHT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,3 Days {\c&Hcd971c&\fs16}   Details
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.55,0:06:14.18,sign_8933_117_Current_Price,TOP SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Current Price
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.09,0:06:15.29,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I prepared myself and registered an account.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.60,sign_8972_119_Place_Bid,ORANGE BUTTON SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Place Bid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.60,sign_8972_120_Seller_Informati,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Seller Information
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.60,sign_8972_121_Follow,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Follow
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.60,sign_8972_122_No_refunds__no_r,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,No refunds, no returns
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.60,sign_8972_123_Overall_Rating__,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Overall Rating: {\c&Hcd971c&}24{\c}   |  Positive Ratings: {\c&Hcd971c&}30
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:17.81,Flashback,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,3,000 yen, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:21.15,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,There were zero bids with \Nthree days left on the auction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:24.09,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Since my time at a computer was limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:25.85,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have time to strategize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.85,0:06:27.56,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I bid immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.56,0:06:29.44,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The price was 3,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:32.45,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was hardly inexpensive for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.45,0:06:35.33,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but it was possible that its price \Nwould rise even higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:40.42,sign_9479_133_Hilarious__Joke_,TOP LEFT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Hilarious! {\c&Ha27428&}Joke Hit Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:40.42,sign_9479_134_Newbies_to_Watch,TOP RIGHT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Newbies to Watch: {\c&H0e0e0e&}The Walrus
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:40.42,sign_9479_135_Short_Skit__Conv,TOP RIGHT SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Short Skit "Convenience Store"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.87,0:06:37.88,Flashback_Italics,CELEBRITY A,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell kind of \Nemployee are you? Enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.88,0:06:41.11,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I erased the history and any other \Ntrace that I'd used the computer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.15,0:06:40.42,Flashback_Italics,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.11,0:06:43.87,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and ate dinner with my family \Nas though nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.87,0:06:45.85,Flashback,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, do we have anything for dessert?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:51.15,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, I felt elated, as though \NI'd become a super hacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:58.46,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.46,0:07:03.92,Flashback,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It went up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.92,0:07:05.58,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I had a rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.58,0:07:07.78,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In retrospect, this piece of shit \Nwas hardly worth it.
