Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:33.58,sign_16530_281_Purchase,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Purchase
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.30,0:11:34.48,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\i0}Zoological Garden{\i1}, \Ncommonly known as "Zooden."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:35.84,sign_16631_285___Back,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,< Back
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:35.84,sign_16631_286_Zoological_Garde,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Zoological Garden
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:35.84,sign_16631_287_Purchase,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Purchase
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:35.84,sign_16631_288_3245_Reviews,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,3245 Reviews
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.48,0:11:37.22,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You raise unique animals \Nand put them in exhibits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.22,0:11:41.49,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,As zoo director, you compete \Nfor ranks on a worldwide scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.96,0:11:45.17,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I had plenty of fun playing \Nas much as I could for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.17,0:11:48.97,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I think collecting erasers back then \Nbecame the basis for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.97,0:11:52.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My rank was awful, but I was \Nhappy when I gained guests,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:57.44,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and when I acquired a rare animal, \Nmy brain tingled dangerously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:11:55.23,sign_17114_295_Super_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(550,1)}Super Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.77,0:11:55.23,sign_17114_296_Snow_Leopard,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Snow Leopard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.27,0:12:00.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,There was a character \NI was determined to acquire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:02.46,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The dodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:08.91,sign_17296_298_Dodo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dodo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:08.91,sign_17296_299_A_now_extinct_sp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,A now-extinct species of bird that once \Nlived on Mauritius Island off of Madagascar. \NDue to its underdeveloped wings, it cannot fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:08.91,sign_17296_300_Attractiveness,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Attractiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:08.91,sign_17296_301_Care_Difficulty,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Care Difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:08.91,sign_17296_302_Maintenance_Cost,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,Maintenance Cost {\c&Hfbff61&}200 fpt {\c}   Exhibit Area {\c&Hebee69&}12 Squares
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:08.91,sign_17296_303_Not_yet_acquired,SIGN BOTTOM LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet acquired!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.79,0:12:05.30,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In the game, the rarity of animals were ranked
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:07.67,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,using terms such as Normal or Rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.67,0:12:09.45,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,As an extinct species,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.45,0:12:11.21,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,the dodo was Special Super Rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:13.13,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it could be pulled \Nfrom the free gacha,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.13,0:12:14.92,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but the odds were extremely low.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.49,0:12:19.90,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Looking back, I took part in eraser \Ncollecting because I had the dodo,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.90,0:12:23.02,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and I was playing Zooden in order \Nto acquire the dodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.02,0:12:24.58,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,When I made that comparison,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.58,0:12:29.34,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I felt as though it was \Nmy destiny to acquire it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:31.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'd spend a little money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.75,0:12:33.43,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I figured that would be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:36.19,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I added 500 yen to my account \Nand pulled the gacha.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:37.65,sign_18075_317_Purchase_Hagenbe,SIGN TOP LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,550)}Purchase Hagenbecks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:37.65,sign_18075_318_6_Hagenbecks,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,550)}6 Hagenbecks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:37.65,sign_18075_319_24_Hagenbecks,SIGN MIDDLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,550)}24 Hagenbecks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:37.65,sign_18075_320_68_Hagenbecks,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,550)}68 Hagenbecks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.98,0:12:42.07,sign_17114_296_Snow_Leopard,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dugong
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:43.55,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The Dugong. Endangered species. Super Rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:42.07,sign_17114_295_Super_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(550,1)}Super Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.55,0:12:46.39,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'd already lost \Nall restraint by this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:48.15,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I looked at my own rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.15,0:12:50.19,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was terrible as usual,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.70,0:12:54.50,sign_18431_329_World_Ranking,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,World Ranking
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.19,0:12:52.72,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but out of curiosity, I looked \Nto see who was number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.72,0:13:02.92,Flashback,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,ditch-11...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.47,0:13:06.93,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was the name that conned me \Nout of 100,000 yen back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.93,0:13:11.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No, maybe it didn't arrive \Nbecause of trouble during shipping.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.23,0:13:15.27,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I bore them no resentment at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:18.20,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't even necessarily the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.68,0:13:20.73,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But. But.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.12,0:13:25.71,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe that it was coincidence \NI'd been reunited with this string of letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.71,0:13:28.20,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that it was destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:31.49,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If I were to take revenge, \Nit would be on my past self.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:34.94,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,And it would be my present self \Nwho would save my past self.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.81,0:13:39.20,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I added 100,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:46.77,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If I were to take revenge, \Nit would be on my past self.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.77,0:13:51.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,And it would be my present self \Nwho would save my past self.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.50,0:13:54.66,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That was four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.66,0:13:57.12,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still playing {\i0}Zooden{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.61,0:13:59.52,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the addition of new systems
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.52,0:14:02.52,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,and events reflecting the real \Nworld keeping the game fresh,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:08.15,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,its content is still popular \Naround the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.88,0:14:08.15,Default - Top,COWORKER F,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.68,0:14:14.16,Default - Top,BOSS B,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to acquire new users \Nwith a new design.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.11,0:14:14.16,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In total, I've spent over \Nfive million yen on this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:16.74,Default - Top,COWORKER I,0000,0000,0000,,We need to capture people's interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.63,0:14:16.74,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My rank is still only in the triple digits.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.74,0:14:18.94,Default - Top,COWORKER D,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we conduct some research?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:18.93,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't have a dodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.93,0:14:19.70,Default,COWORKER H,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:21.14,Default,COWORKER G,0000,0000,0000,,We're spending our budget on research?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:23.33,Default,COWORKER E,0000,0000,0000,,But we have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.33,0:14:25.63,Default,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tanaka. Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.87,0:14:28.00,Default,COWORKER B,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:29.48,Default,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.48,0:14:30.14,Default,COWORKER A,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.14,0:14:30.88,Default,COWORKER D,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.88,0:14:31.88,Default - Top,COWORKER E,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:33.98,Italics,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The bird that went extinct \Nwithout ever learning to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.88,0:14:33.13,Default - Top,COWORKER H,0000,0000,0000,,Tanaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:36.66,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I was projecting myself onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.66,0:14:38.66,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was just like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.66,0:14:43.44,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No, if I died here without achieving \Nanything, I wouldn't even be Rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.44,0:14:44.98,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be just Normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:46.90,sign_21219_371_Buy_Sell_Zoologi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Buy/Sell Zoological Garden Account
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:46.90,sign_21219_372_Purchase,SIGN ORANGE BUTTON,0000,0000,0000,,Purchase
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:46.90,sign_21219_374_Account_with_num,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Account with numerous Super Rare characters\N {\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: tarou\N\N\N {\c&H0000b1&\fs16}First come, first served! \N3 Super Rare characters \N {\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: sakio \N\N\N{\c&H0000b1&\fs16}Assortment of 5 Super Rare characters\N {\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: kinopi_22{\c}{\fs}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.86,0:14:48.50,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,As a game that enjoys worldwide popularity,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:49.95,sign_21266_378_Account_with_10_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Account with 10 3-star characters \N{\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: yakitori45\N\N{\c&H0000b1&\fs16}Great deal! Account \Nwith numerous endangered species\N{\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: tarou\N\N{\c&H0000b1&\fs16}First come, first served! \N10 Super Rare characters\N{\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: kondo11\N\N{\c&H0000b1&\fs16}Assortment of 20 Limited Rare characters\N{\b0\c&H8B8B8B&\fs13}Seller: kitanotakeshifan{\c}{\fs}{\c}{\fs}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.50,0:14:50.39,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,its market size is naturally large.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.39,0:14:54.20,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,There are even intermediaries \Nwho buy and sell entire accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:58.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My triple-digit-ranked account \Nthat I've spend over five million yen on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.23,0:15:00.53,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,would only sell for a few hundred thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.53,0:15:03.11,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If ditch-11's account \Nappeared on the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.11,0:15:04.48,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,it would go for a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:10.69,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,An account with a dodo could be mine \Nfor several tens of thousands of yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.69,0:15:13.14,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not it. It's not the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.49,0:15:16.01,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,"What is it about, then?" I ask myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.51,0:15:19.66,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The romance? The catharsis?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.66,0:15:21.15,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The release from oppression?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:22.48,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The need for social recognition?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.48,0:15:24.11,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The desire to feel superior to one's peers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:26.71,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I try on gussied-up words \Nand phrases for size.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.67,0:15:30.54,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No. The truth is, I already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.54,0:15:34.23,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I know those fancy words don't apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.23,0:15:36.83,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's simpler than that. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.94,0:15:40.56,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A sickness. It's a sickness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:41.92,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.92,0:15:43.96,Default,COWORKER C,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:47.94,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd begun spending tens of thousands of \Nyen on the game like it was nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.50,0:15:50.17,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was completely numb.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:52.47,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Everything I did was \Nto get my hands on a dodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.96,0:15:56.13,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,To get revenge on the boy \NI was 16 years ago and save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:58.29,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,And to get closer to ditch-11,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.29,0:16:01.49,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,who continues to reign \Nfrom the number one spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.49,0:16:04.62,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You just wait, ditch-11.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.11,sign_23322_410_Super_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(550,1)}Super Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.11,sign_23322_411_Red_Panda,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Red Panda
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:17.62,sign_23410_412_Super_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(550,1)}Super Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:17.62,sign_23410_413_Okapi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Okapi
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.54,sign_23595_414_Ultra_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Ultra Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.54,sign_23595_415_Dodo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dodo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:34.30,sign_23759_416_Ultra_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Ultra Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:34.30,sign_23759_417_Dodo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dodo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:38.64,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A dodo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.64,0:16:40.97,sign_23944_419_Ultra_Rare,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Ultra Rare
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.64,0:16:40.97,sign_23944_420_Dodo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dodo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.30,0:16:41.65,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My four years...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:46.40,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No, my 16 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:48.94,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It finally paid off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.94,0:16:54.07,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I did it! A dodo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:21.46,Default,CLERK,0000,0000,0000,,Your backed up data \Nhas been restored—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:28.72,sign_25119_427_Snow_Leopard,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Snow Leopard
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:28.72,sign_25119_428_Dugong,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dugong
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:28.72,sign_25119_429_Dodo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dodo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:32.23,sign_25119_426_Animal_List,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Animal List
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:32.23,sign_25159_430_Dodo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Dodo
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.55,0:17:38.70,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My mind went blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.70,0:17:40.85,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.85,0:17:42.49,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember walking home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.38,0:17:46.45,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The loss I felt over the dodo \NI had definitely acquired
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.45,0:17:48.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,robbed me of all my willpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:56.39,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But fate is cruel, and God had \Ntaken something else from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.89,0:18:04.94,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's when the blue flame \Ninside of me finally came to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.75,0:18:09.19,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least, it wasn't God \Nwho took my dodo from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:10.90,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It was that taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.78,0:18:15.03,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though someone \Ntook Maru from me, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.03,0:18:17.54,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The life expectancy of a \Ncockatiel is about 15 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.54,0:18:19.35,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,He lived a full life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:22.50,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It just happened to be today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.50,0:18:26.50,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But sometimes, thinking about \Nthis unfortunate coincidence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.50,0:18:29.61,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,makes me wonder if there is a God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.39,0:18:33.92,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,In games, often the player \Nacquires a valuable item
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.92,0:18:36.13,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,just when they think \Nthey've reached a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.13,0:18:39.18,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's convenient. Of course it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:41.22,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, somebody made it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.87,0:18:44.45,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Then there must be someone \Nwho made this world, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.45,0:18:47.48,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this world has been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.99,0:18:52.34,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, God. It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.96,0:18:56.40,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,This happened three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:06.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Taxi... Kill... Maru... Dodo...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.11,0:19:10.82,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Ow. Hold on, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:13.09,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize when you bump into someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.09,0:19:14.70,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.65,0:19:17.01,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.93,0:19:23.35,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait. Hold on, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.35,0:19:26.39,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? You've got \Nthe face of a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.05,0:19:30.40,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I'm just curious \Ndue to the nature of my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.40,0:19:34.01,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you. You're from the countryside. \NWhy'd you come out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.01,0:19:35.16,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The countryside?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.16,0:19:37.86,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I guess compared to Tokyo, \Nit is the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.62,0:19:40.49,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you chasing a dream or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.49,0:19:45.00,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I came to Tokyo for\N status, glory, and big money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.72,0:19:48.24,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But, you still haven't gotten those.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.24,0:19:50.75,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Rome wasn't built in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:52.58,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you need \Nto do to get them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.87,0:19:55.32,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If I knew that, my life would be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.32,0:19:57.63,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,My partner said it's luck, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.63,0:19:59.01,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Your partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.01,0:20:01.28,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's like my business partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.89,0:20:04.68,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Luck, huh? You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:07.05,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe luck is involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.05,0:20:10.08,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't want to give up \Non the things I can control.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.08,0:20:12.39,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,There's plenty to consider besides luck
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.39,0:20:14.52,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,when trying to figure out how to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.52,0:20:17.13,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying the dodo was unlucky, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.13,0:20:17.94,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.60,0:20:23.87,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.87,0:20:26.05,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you and I were \Nfollowing the same road.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:28.22,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me we were actually \Non the highway and subway?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.28,0:20:34.35,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I've always been \Nsearching for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.35,0:20:38.79,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, my life has \Nalways been lacking something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.23,0:20:44.50,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,And desperately acquiring that something \Nyields only a moment of pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.47,0:20:47.72,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Far from being good fortune,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.23,0:20:52.04,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,it's simply a moment of pleasure \Nproduced by the release of dopamine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.83,0:20:55.10,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:59.58,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The single word that always follows \Nafter I've acquired something I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.07,0:21:01.21,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,"And?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:05.62,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,"So, what?" my other self asks me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.62,0:21:08.44,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's always there, \Nhand-in-hand with nihilism.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.44,0:21:11.37,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,A truly formless pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.94,0:21:15.62,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, I'm experiencing being alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.62,0:21:19.82,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I found what I wanted \Nthe moment I lost my dodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.22,0:21:21.64,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike before,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.64,0:21:24.28,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,it wasn't just an addition to my \Ncollection that ended once acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.79,0:21:27.66,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What shall I do next?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.66,0:21:30.26,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Just thinking about it excites me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.26,0:21:32.40,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Rare Item with \Npotential for development.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.21,0:21:36.28,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I believe everyone possesses \Nthe impulse to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.28,0:21:39.48,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,An impulse to attack that's \Nmore exciting and justified
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:42.55,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,the less you are to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:45.84,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I've been walking for three days since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.26,0:21:50.03,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to chasing odds \Nfar more mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.62,0:21:52.24,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But this time, it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.24,0:21:54.74,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I felt something like a premonition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.74,0:21:57.61,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, I said that I could seize it \Nif I let go of my attachments,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.61,0:22:00.75,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but there's another way \Nto acquire what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.53,0:22:05.26,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,And that is by holding tightly
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.26,0:22:08.40,Italics,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,onto a powerful attachment \Nthat transcends all else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.57,0:22:14.90,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you! What are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.97,0:23:50.61,Next_Time,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time: {\fs22\b1}Don't Call Me an Idol{\fs\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.61,0:23:37.78,Default - Top,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've never actually seen \Nsomeone point them all out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.78,0:23:40.02,Default - Top,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}when they say something \Nis full of mistakes or flaws.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.02,0:23:42.85,Default - Top,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why don't you carefully verbalize \Neach and every one of them, huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.85,0:23:44.33,Default - Top,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Probably too stupid to do it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.33,0:23:45.70,Default - Top,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're pretty drunk.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:47.46,Default - Top,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Man, maybe I'll win the lottery.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.46,0:23:49.52,Default - Top,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your job is like a lottery.{\i0}